RACE.RACE_TEXT: SUFFOLK DOWNS RACE 1 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 51. Maiden Claiming Purse 9000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EL COVER dueled on the outside to the backstretch, veered in to the rail, dueled inside from the five-eighths pole and drew off near the final furlong under steady urging. TIME FOR HONOR dueled to the backstretch, steadied and hit the rail, angled outside to duel with the winner again and weakened in the upper stretch. WHITE QUEEN stumbled badly at the start and was far back early, saved ground advancing on the second turn but was no threat to the top pair. DEL MAR SURF pressed the pace on the outside into the backstretch and then was through early. CONCORDE'S QUEEN was outrun . MADDY'S PARADE pressed the pace on the inside and tired. WILD ASPEN FLOWER raced four- then three-wide on the first turn and gave way after a half. AFTER THE RIDER OF TIME FOR HONOR CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST THE RIDER OF EL COVER, ALLEGING INTERFERENCE ENTERING THE BACKSTRETCH, THE STEWARDS REVIEWED THE INCIDENT AND ALLOWED THE RESULT TO STAND.
